omist.com/cdn-cgi/image/width=1424,quality=80,format=auto/media-assets/image/20230623_FLP002.jpg 1424w" src="https://www.economist.com/cdn-cgi/image/width=1424,quality=80,format=auto/media-assets/image/20230623_FLP002.jpg" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></figure></section><p data-caps="initial" class="article__body-text article__body-text--dropcap"><span data-caps="initial">凯文</span>·卡劳尔 (Kevin Kallaugher)<small>以 KAL 为</small>笔名，为<i>《经济学人》</i>绘图 45 年。在这里，我们的镜头捕捉到了 KAL 正在制作他的每周漫画，他讨论了描绘中国领导人所面临的挑战。 </p><p class="article__body-text"><iframe height="360" src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/5_BovmrW5GA?enablejsapi=1" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></iframe></p> ]]>;</description><pubDate> Fri, 23 Jun 2023 18:16:26 GMT</pubDate><guid ispermalink="false"> /内容/8fn9btl93p86efloesj9an22mb40u77g</guid><link/> https://www.economist.com/films/2023/06/23/our-cartoonist-on-caricaturing-xi </item><item><title><![CDATA[Britons love country fairs. Why?]]></title><description><![CDATA[<section class="css-1ugvd2u e1y6i3a60"><style data-emotion="css j1vyw6">.css-j1vyw6 img{display:block;}.css-j1vyw6 .e16qazw92{margin-top:0.25rem;}</style><figure class="css-j1vyw6 e12yhaj20"><img alt="2022 年 6 月 26 日，在爱丁堡皇家高地中心举行的皇家高地展盛大游行中，牛群亮相。" fetchpriority="high" width="1280" height="720" decoding="async" data-nimg="1" style="color:transparent" sizes="(min-width: 960px) 700px, 95vw" srcset="https://www.economist.com/cdn-cgi/image/width=360,quality=80,format=auto/content-assets/images/20230624_BRP504.jpg 360w, https://www.economist.com/cdn-cgi/image/width=384,quality=80,format=auto/content-assets/images/20230624_BRP504.jpg 384w, https://www.economist.com/cdn-cgi/image/width=480,quality=80,format=auto/content-assets/images/20230624_BRP504.jpg 480w, https://www.economist.com/cdn-cgi/image/width=600,quality=80,format=auto/content-assets/images/20230624_BRP504.jpg 600w, https://www.economist.com/cdn-cgi/image/width=834,quality=80,format=auto/content-assets/images/20230624_BRP504.jpg 834w, https://www.economist.com/cdn-cgi/image/width=960,quality=80,format=auto/content-assets/images/20230624_BRP504.jpg 960w, https://www.economist.com/cdn-cgi/image/width=1096,quality=80,format=auto/content-assets/images/20230624_BRP504.jpg 1096w, https://www.economist.com/cdn-cgi/image/width=1280,quality=80,format=auto/content-assets/images/20230624_BRP504.jpg 1280w, https://www.economist.com/cdn-cgi/image/width=1424,quality=80,format=auto/content-assets/images/20230624_BRP504.jpg 1424w" src="https://www.economist.com/cdn-cgi/image/width=1424,quality=80,format=auto/content-assets/images/20230624_BRP504.jpg" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"><style data-emotion="css 18w36g1">.css-18w36g1{width:100%;font-family:var(--ds-type-system-sans);}</style><figcaption class="css-18w36g1 e16qazw92"><style data-emotion="css 48en16">.css-48en16{font-family:var(--ds-type-system-sans-smallcaps);font-size:var(--ds-type-scale--1);font-weight:400;font-variant-ligatures:none;line-height:var(--ds-type-leading-lower);text-transform:lowercase;color:var(--ds-color-london-35);}</style><!-- --><span class="css-48en16 e16qazw91">图片：盖蒂图片社</span></figcaption></figure></section><p data-caps="initial" class="article__body-text article__body-text--dropcap"> <span data-caps="initial">NGUS</span> <small>NEISH</small>敢于希望他在威尔特郡罗德米德农场饲养的漂亮牛能够在 6 月 3 日的皇家巴斯和西部展上获奖。一年一度的博览会在萨默塞特郡谢普顿马利特附近举行，是英格兰历史最悠久、规模最大的博览会。除了竞争激烈的牲畜游行外，还有莫里斯舞蹈、剪羊毛和老式游乐场。与此同时，它的小马战车比赛也是首屈一指的。最近的一个下午，许多参赛者首先在附近的苹果酒帐篷里进行了慷慨的定制。他们在一大群人面前进行了激烈的表演。</p><p class="article__body-text">英国人喜欢集市。部分归功于晴朗的天气，为期三天的展会部分观众人数达到 10 万人。没有人确切知道到底有多少个集市，但每年至少有 400 天发生此类乡村活动。去年的议会简报显示，每年大约有十分之一的英国人参加这些活动。看来他们的受欢迎程度正在上升。像去年大约克郡秀那样，门票全部售空的活动可能会变得更加常见。 </p><div class="adComponent_advert__V79Pp adComponent_incontent__Bxd2J adComponent_hidden___o_ZB advert--inline"><div><div id="econ-1" class="adComponent_adcontainer__dO1Zm"></div></div></div><p class="article__body-text">本周末，爱丁堡附近将举行皇家高地秀 (Royal Highland Show)，预计参观人数将超过 20 万人，很可能超过 2019 年创下的纪录。它们对当地产生了显着的影响，每年六月底都会定期带来经济增长。据估计，去年的这一活动为当地经济带来了近 4000 万英镑（5100 万美元）的增长。</p><p class="article__body-text">有何吸引力？怀旧显然是一个很大的吸引力。在巴斯和韦斯特，随着彩旗飘扬，游客们有序地排队，购买奶油茶，聆听军乐队演奏战时热门歌曲。但乡村表演也有其目的，甚至不仅仅是将游客送进苹果酒或威士忌帐篷。许多博览会创办于 18 或 19 世纪，目的是向农村人口传播新农业技术的知识。其中一些任务仍在继续。对于 Neish 先生这样的人来说，600 个贸易摊位至少与任何莫里斯舞蹈一样有趣。</p><p class="article__body-text">第二个目标是更好地教育城市游客，城市游客在前来参观的游客中占了相当大的比例。一些消费者还拥有丰富的食品供应链知识，有时对有机、本地、动物友好型、纯素食、公平贸易和环保产品有着复杂的个人偏好。皇家威尔士秀的劳拉·威廉姆斯指出，与过去几年相比，如今的游客“对农业投入更多，并对食物的来源感兴趣”。</p><p class="article__body-text">最后一个目的自然是让农民在友好竞争中战胜对手。从这方面来说，尼什先生度过了非常成功的一天。这是巴斯和韦斯特的第一次，他的牛获得了各自类别中所有四个最高奖项。这些胜利不会带来立竿见影的巨额经济回报，但可能会大大提升他的育种计划的声誉。 “这对我来说是一个很好的广告方式，”他笑着说道。 <span data-ornament="ufinish">■</span></p><p class="article__body-text"><i>如需对英国重大新闻进行更多专家分析，<a href="https://www.economist.com/newsletters/blighty">请订阅</a>我们的订阅者每周通讯 Blighty。</i></p> ]]>;</description><pubDate> Fri, 23 Jun 2023 16:45:34 GMT</pubDate><guid ispermalink="false"> /内容/bl05dn10tpmdgfh5v4hbgpk57vch50rf</guid><link/> https://www.economist.com/britain/2023/06/23/britons-love-country-fairs-why </item><item><title><![CDATA[What effect has the end of Roe v Wade had on abortion access?]]></title><description><![CDATA[<section class="css-1ugvd2u e1y6i3a60"><style data-emotion="css j1vyw6">.css-j1vyw6 img{display:block;}.css-j1vyw6 .e16qazw92{margin-top:0.25rem;}</style><figure class="css-j1vyw6 e12yhaj20"><img alt="" fetchpriority="high" width="1280" height="720" decoding="async" data-nimg="1" style="color:transparent" sizes="(min-width: 960px) 700px, 95vw" srcset="https://www.economist.com/cdn-cgi/image/width=360,quality=80,format=auto/media-assets/image/20230624_PDP510.jpg 360w, https://www.economist.com/cdn-cgi/image/width=384,quality=80,format=auto/media-assets/image/20230624_PDP510.jpg 384w, https://www.economist.com/cdn-cgi/image/width=480,quality=80,format=auto/media-assets/image/20230624_PDP510.jpg 480w, https://www.economist.com/cdn-cgi/image/width=600,quality=80,format=auto/media-assets/image/20230624_PDP510.jpg 600w, https://www.economist.com/cdn-cgi/image/width=834,quality=80,format=auto/media-assets/image/20230624_PDP510.jpg 834w, https://www.economist.com/cdn-cgi/image/width=960,quality=80,format=auto/media-assets/image/20230624_PDP510.jpg 960w, https://www.economist.com/cdn-cgi/image/width=1096,quality=80,format=auto/media-assets/image/20230624_PDP510.jpg 1096w, https://www.economist.com/cdn-cgi/image/width=1280,quality=80,format=auto/media-assets/image/20230624_PDP510.jpg 1280w, https://www.economist.com/cdn-cgi/image/width=1424,quality=80,format=auto/media-assets/image/20230624_PDP510.jpg 1424w" src="https://www.economist.com/cdn-cgi/image/width=1424,quality=80,format=auto/media-assets/image/20230624_PDP510.jpg" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></figure></section><p class="article__body-text">一年前，最高法院推翻了美国的堕胎准入。法院<a href="https://www.economist.com/united-states/2022/06/24/the-supreme-court-erases-the-constitutional-right-to-abortion">推翻<i>罗伊诉韦德</i></a>案的决定允许各州禁止堕胎，从而导致全国各地的政策杂乱无章。这项裁决实际上产生了什么影响？ <a href="https://www.economist.com/united-states/2023/06/22/one-year-after-dobbs-americas-pro-life-movement-is-in-flux">堕胎权之争</a>接下来会发生什么？</p><p class="article__body-text">计划生育协会的 Ushma Upadhyay 博士分享了最新数据。 《从后巷到边境》一书的作者艾丽西亚·古铁雷斯-罗明博士记得罗纳德·里根在扩大堕胎机会方面所发挥的令人惊讶的作用。 <i>《经济学人</i>》的史蒂夫·赫兹前往俄亥俄州，那里的选民被要求决定该州堕胎权的未来。</p><p class="article__body-text">约翰·普里多 (John Prideaux) 与夏洛特·霍华德 (Charlotte Howard) 和伊德里斯·卡隆 (Idrees Kahloon) 共同主持。</p><p class="article__body-text">时长：45分钟</p><p class="article__body-text"><iframe height="215" src="https://embed.acast.com/checksandbalance/checks-and-balance-roe-away" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></iframe></p><p class="article__body-text">我们很高兴听到您对《经济学人》播客的看法。如果您有几分钟时间，请填写我们的最新调查： <a href="http://economist.com/podcastsurvey/">economics.com/podcastsurvey</a> 。</p><p class="article__body-text">现在，您可以<a href="https://www.economist.com/checkspod">在一个地方</a>找到《制衡》的每一集，并订阅我们的每周时事<a href="https://www.economist.com/newsletters">通讯</a>。如需完全访问印刷版、数字版和音频版以及独家现场活动，请通过<a href="http://economist.com/uspod/">coneconomicist.com/uspod</a>订阅《经济学人》。</p> ]]>;</description><pubDate> Fri, 23 Jun 2023 16:33:27 GMT</pubDate><guid ispermalink="false"> /内容/u01qj7tcd1cvkuqefiivv477trvbs9n8</guid><link/> https://www.economist.com/podcasts/2023/06/23/what-effect-has-the-end-of-roe-v-wade-had-on-abortion-access </item><item><title><![CDATA[Dobbs electrified supporters of abortion rights]]></title><description><![CDATA[<div class="css-phnw8u ex4i8i00"><style data-emotion="css j1vyw6">.css-j1vyw6 img{display:block;}.css-j1vyw6 .e16qazw92{margin-top:0.25rem;}</style><figure class="css-j1vyw6 e12yhaj20"><img theme="[object Object]" alt="" loading="lazy" width="1280" height="720" decoding="async" data-nimg="1" style="color:transparent" sizes="(min-width: 1440px) 700px, (min-width: 1280px) 50vw, (min-width: 960px) 66vw, 95vw" srcset="https://www.economist.com/img/b/256/144/90/media-assets/image/20230624_WOT558.png 256w, https://www.economist.com/img/b/360/202/90/media-assets/image/20230624_WOT558.png 360w, https://www.economist.com/img/b/384/216/90/media-assets/image/20230624_WOT558.png 384w, https://www.economist.com/img/b/480/270/90/media-assets/image/20230624_WOT558.png 480w, https://www.economist.com/img/b/600/337/90/media-assets/image/20230624_WOT558.png 600w, https://www.economist.com/img/b/834/469/90/media-assets/image/20230624_WOT558.png 834w, https://www.economist.com/img/b/960/540/90/media-assets/image/20230624_WOT558.png 960w, https://www.economist.com/img/b/1096/616/90/media-assets/image/20230624_WOT558.png 1096w, https://www.economist.com/img/b/1280/720/90/media-assets/image/20230624_WOT558.png 1280w, https://www.economist.com/img/b/1424/801/90/media-assets/image/20230624_WOT558.png 1424w" src="https://www.economist.com/img/b/1424/801/90/media-assets/image/20230624_WOT558.png" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></figure></div><style data-emotion="css tati6o">.css-tati6o{font-family:var(--ds-type-system-serif);font-size:var(--ds-type-scale-4);font-weight:normal;line-height:var(--ds-type-leading-upper);}.css-tati6o a{-webkit-text-decoration:none;text-decoration:none;color:var(--ds-color-london-5);display:block;}.css-tati6o a:hover,.css-tati6o a:hover .efv3iwx0{color:var(--ds-color-chicago-30);-webkit-text-decoration:underline;text-decoration:underline;}.css-tati6o a:focus,.css-tati6o a:focus .efv3iwx0{background-color:var(--ds-color-chicago-95);color:var(--ds-color-london-5);outline:none;-webkit-text-decoration:underline;text-decoration:underline;}.css-tati6o a:active,.css-tati6o a:active .efv3iwx0{color:var(--ds-color-chicago-30);}.css-tati6o a::before{bottom:0;content:'';display:block;left:0;opacity:0;overflow:hidden;position:absolute;right:0;text-indent:-999em;top:0;white-space:nowrap;z-index:1;}.css-tati6o+.e1dj3j7p0,.css-tati6o+style+.e1dj3j7p0{margin-top:0.5rem;}.e1wqg93o0 .css-tati6o+.e1dj3j7p0{margin-top:0;}</style><h3 class="css-tati6o eifj80y0"> <a href="https://www.economist.com/graphic-detail/2023/06/22/supply-chains-are-back-to-normal-why-is-inflation-still-so-high" data-analytics="more_from:headline_1">供应链已恢复正常。为什么通货膨胀仍然如此之高？</a> </h3><style data-emotion="css 1tj7b79">.css-1tj7b79{color:var(--ds-color-london-10);font-family:var(--ds-type-system-serif);max-width:43.75rem;font-size:1.125rem;line-height:var(--ds-type-leading-lower);}.e13odduf0 .css-1tj7b79{font-size:var(--ds-type-scale-2);}</style><p class="css-1tj7b79 e1dj3j7p0">新冠疫情造成的干扰和能源价格飙升可能导致持续的价格压力</p><p class="article__body-text"><i>要阅读《经济学人》数据新闻的更多内容，请访问我们的<a href="https://www.economist.com/graphic-detail/">图形详细信息</a>页面。</i></p><p data-caps="initial" class="article__body-text article__body-text--dropcap">美国妇女<span data-caps="initial">一旦</span>失去宪法规定<small>的</small>堕胎权，路易斯安那州就实施了该国一些最严厉的限制。于是，28 岁的新奥尔良人凡妮莎开始制定输卵管结扎计划。最近的堕胎诊所现在位于伊利诺伊州，距离酒店有 12 小时车程，她知道如果她意外怀孕，她就无法请假去那里。她说，“未经父亲或男朋友的同意”，当地医生拒绝给她绝育（尽管没有这样的法律要求），但最终她在 TikTok 上找到了一位注册妇科医生，她会这么做。到了夏末，她已经不孕了。 </p><figure class="g-fallback" data-infographic-class="g-fallback"></figure><figure class="interactive-figure"><iframe height="NaN" src="https://infographics.economist.com/2023/20230624_WOM937/" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></iframe></figure><p class="article__body-text"> <a href="https://www.economist.com/united-states/2023/06/22/one-year-after-dobbs-americas-pro-life-movement-is-in-flux">一年前</a>，最高法院在<i>多布斯诉杰克逊妇女健康组织一案中裁定，</i>各州将成为堕胎政策的仲裁者。此后，14 个国家彻底禁止堕胎，6 个国家将怀孕时间限制在 6 至 20 周之间。三分之一的美国育龄女性现在必须开车一个多小时才能接受手术。对于距离诊所最远的得克萨斯州科珀斯克里斯蒂市的人来说，路程要超过 15 个小时（见图表）。</p><p class="article__body-text">根据非营利组织计划生育协会的数据，2022 年 7 月至 2023 年 3 月期间，超过 25,000 名寻求堕胎的人无法终止妊娠。 （自<i>多布斯</i>以来，平均每月有 79,000 例堕胎。）但手术堕胎的下降被邮寄堕胎的急剧上升所抵消。今年 4 月，最高法院裁定堕胎药物可以保留在药房货架上，至少目前如此，这让生育权运动松了口气，尽管对于生活在有禁令的州的女性来说，网上订购药物仍然是非法的。 </p><div class="adComponent_advert__V79Pp adComponent_incontent__Bxd2J adComponent_hidden___o_ZB advert--inline"><div><div id="econ-1" class="adComponent_adcontainer__dO1Zm"></div></div></div><div class="article__body-text-image"><figure><meta itemprop="url" content="https://www.economist.com/img/b/1280/1451/90/media-assets/image/20230624_WOC602.png"> <span itemscope="" itemprop="image" itemtype="https://schema.org/ImageObject" data-slim="1"><img loading="lazy" src="https://www.economist.com/img/b/1280/1451/90/media-assets/image/20230624_WOC602.png" srcset="https://www.economist.com/img/b/200/227/90/media-assets/image/20230624_WOC602.png 200w,https://www.economist.com/img/b/300/340/90/media-assets/image/20230624_WOC602.png 300w,https://www.economist.com/img/b/400/453/90/media-assets/image/20230624_WOC602.png 400w,https://www.economist.com/img/b/600/680/90/media-assets/image/20230624_WOC602.png 600w,https://www.economist.com/img/b/640/726/90/media-assets/image/20230624_WOC602.png 640w,https://www.economist.com/img/b/800/907/90/media-assets/image/20230624_WOC602.png 800w,https://www.economist.com/img/b/1000/1134/90/media-assets/image/20230624_WOC602.png 1000w,https://www.economist.com/img/b/1280/1451/90/media-assets/image/20230624_WOC602.png 1280w" sizes="336px" alt="" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></span></figure><p class="article__body-text">共和党削减堕胎率的运动让堕胎权的支持者兴奋不已。在<i>多布斯去世</i>后的几周内，名人和其他捐助者承诺为这项事业提供数百万美元。表示支持合法堕胎的美国人比例有所上升，即使是在妊娠晚期。各派民主党人都联合起来反对共和党的堕胎政策。这种势头是新的。在保守派赢得最高法院多数席位之前，美国人对这个问题的看法与政治立场远不一致。研究机构公共宗教研究所进行的一项调查显示，2018 年，那些希望禁止堕胎的人中，38% 的人自称是民主党人，而自称共和党人的比例为 36%。到 2023 年 4 月，反对堕胎的民主党人比例骤降至 14%；共和党人的支持率则上升至 49%。</p><p class="article__body-text">堕胎权活动人士渴望尽可能将堕胎纳入选票，因为选民倾向于保护堕胎。但在共和党占立法多数的州，立法者正在通过越来越严格的法案，尽管在某些地方这可能会损害他们的选举。对于这些州的堕胎权利倡导者来说，这感觉就像是一记重击。 “他们拥有一切，”路易斯安那州民权组织“正义承诺倡议”的凯蒂·亨特·洛瑞说道。 “我不知道他们还想从我们这里得到什么肉。” <span data-ornament="ufinish">■</span></p></div> ]]>;</description><pubDate> Fri, 23 Jun 2023 16:14:05 GMT</pubDate><guid ispermalink="false"> /内容/h34k01m8k78754eho6uboj0836oj3b1d</guid><link/> https://www.economist.com/graphic-detail/2023/06/23/dobbs-electrified-supporters-of-abortion-rights </item><item><title><![CDATA[Infighting is breaking out among Russia’s military chiefs]]></title><description><![CDATA[<section class="css-1ugvd2u e1y6i3a60"><style data-emotion="css j1vyw6">.css-j1vyw6 img{display:block;}.css-j1vyw6 .e16qazw92{margin-top:0.25rem;}</style><figure class="css-j1vyw6 e12yhaj20"><img alt="俄罗斯历史二战周年纪念阅兵普京" fetchpriority="high" width="1280" height="720" decoding="async" data-nimg="1" style="color:transparent" sizes="(min-width: 960px) 700px, 95vw" srcset="https://www.economist.com/cdn-cgi/image/width=360,quality=80,format=auto/media-assets/image/20230623_FLP001.jpg 360w, https://www.economist.com/cdn-cgi/image/width=384,quality=80,format=auto/media-assets/image/20230623_FLP001.jpg 384w, https://www.economist.com/cdn-cgi/image/width=480,quality=80,format=auto/media-assets/image/20230623_FLP001.jpg 480w, https://www.economist.com/cdn-cgi/image/width=600,quality=80,format=auto/media-assets/image/20230623_FLP001.jpg 600w, https://www.economist.com/cdn-cgi/image/width=834,quality=80,format=auto/media-assets/image/20230623_FLP001.jpg 834w, https://www.economist.com/cdn-cgi/image/width=960,quality=80,format=auto/media-assets/image/20230623_FLP001.jpg 960w, https://www.economist.com/cdn-cgi/image/width=1096,quality=80,format=auto/media-assets/image/20230623_FLP001.jpg 1096w, https://www.economist.com/cdn-cgi/image/width=1280,quality=80,format=auto/media-assets/image/20230623_FLP001.jpg 1280w, https://www.economist.com/cdn-cgi/image/width=1424,quality=80,format=auto/media-assets/image/20230623_FLP001.jpg 1424w" src="https://www.economist.com/cdn-cgi/image/width=1424,quality=80,format=auto/media-assets/image/20230623_FLP001.jpg" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></figure></section><p data-caps="initial" class="article__body-text article__body-text--dropcap"><span data-caps="initial">乌克兰</span><small>的反攻</small>暴露了俄罗斯军事领导层的裂痕。在莫斯科周边居民区发生一系列无人机袭击后，瓦格纳雇佣军组织创始人叶夫根尼·普里戈任在社交媒体上批评战争策略，挑战克里姆林宫的正统观念。在这段视频中，我们探讨了为什么不和谐的程度看起来会加剧。 </p><p class="article__body-text"><iframe height="360" src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/iAPBBeHQy_o?enablejsapi=1" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></iframe></p> ]]>;</description><pubDate> Fri, 23 Jun 2023 15:32:20 GMT</pubDate><guid ispermalink="false"> /内容/1jro1lcpbp7u11s2b054grq2fn640n2t</guid><link/> https://www.economist.com/films/2023/06/23/infighting-is-breaking-out-among-Russias-military-chiefs </item><item><title><![CDATA[One year after a revolutionary abortion ruling, are America’s pro-lifers splintering?]]></title><description><![CDATA[<section class="css-1ugvd2u e1y6i3a60"><style data-emotion="css j1vyw6">.css-j1vyw6 img{display:block;}.css-j1vyw6 .e16qazw92{margin-top:0.25rem;}</style><figure class="css-j1vyw6 e12yhaj20"><img alt="" fetchpriority="high" width="1280" height="720" decoding="async" data-nimg="1" style="color:transparent" sizes="(min-width: 960px) 700px, 95vw" srcset="https://www.economist.com/cdn-cgi/image/width=360,quality=80,format=auto/media-assets/image/20230624_PDP509.jpg 360w, https://www.economist.com/cdn-cgi/image/width=384,quality=80,format=auto/media-assets/image/20230624_PDP509.jpg 384w, https://www.economist.com/cdn-cgi/image/width=480,quality=80,format=auto/media-assets/image/20230624_PDP509.jpg 480w, https://www.economist.com/cdn-cgi/image/width=600,quality=80,format=auto/media-assets/image/20230624_PDP509.jpg 600w, https://www.economist.com/cdn-cgi/image/width=834,quality=80,format=auto/media-assets/image/20230624_PDP509.jpg 834w, https://www.economist.com/cdn-cgi/image/width=960,quality=80,format=auto/media-assets/image/20230624_PDP509.jpg 960w, https://www.economist.com/cdn-cgi/image/width=1096,quality=80,format=auto/media-assets/image/20230624_PDP509.jpg 1096w, https://www.economist.com/cdn-cgi/image/width=1280,quality=80,format=auto/media-assets/image/20230624_PDP509.jpg 1280w, https://www.economist.com/cdn-cgi/image/width=1424,quality=80,format=auto/media-assets/image/20230624_PDP509.jpg 1424w" src="https://www.economist.com/cdn-cgi/image/width=1424,quality=80,format=auto/media-assets/image/20230624_PDP509.jpg" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></figure></section><p class="article__body-text">自从美国最高法院赋予各州禁止堕胎的权力以来的几个月里，支持这一裁决的人变得<a href="https://www.economist.com/united-states/2023/06/22/one-year-after-dobbs-americas-pro-life-movement-is-in-flux" data-tegid="bmud9k4encui53l8j04m8odir7b9olom">更加分裂</a>。在左派语言的帮助下，他们正在招募新成员。关于<a href="https://www.economist.com/science-and-technology/2023/06/08/a-tiny-ancient-hominin-may-have-been-surprisingly-clever" data-tegid="q0ptb1s1tc9cp85ag9amnnkf6l1ip4ir">类人物种</a>智力的新发现正在改变我们对进化的理解。并且，向泄露<a href="https://www.economist.com/obituary/2023/06/21/daniel-ellsberg-leaked-the-pentagon-papers-to-try-to-stop-the-vietnam-war" data-tegid="0v6u86k4mrnbclqi08cjlsnf0qj47rro">五角大楼文件</a>的人​​致敬。时长：28分钟</p><p class="article__body-text"><iframe height="215" src="https://embed.acast.com/theintelligencepodcast/pro-life-post-dobbs-americas-anti-abortion-campaigns" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></iframe></p><p class="article__body-text">收听： <a href="https://podcasts.apple.com/us/podcast/the-intelligence-from-the-economist/id1449631195">Apple 播客</a>| <a href="https://open.spotify.com/show/12zKAMNyS2GNentUzxq9QN">Spotify</a>